briefdescription.para: Activates the Ethernet controller.

detaileddescription.para: Upon activation of the controller, the controller attempts to establish a link. Messages can only be sent once the link has been successfully established,

parameterdescription.para: The Ethernet controller to be activated.

simplesect.para: A return code identifying the success/failure of the call.

briefdescription.para: Deactivate the Ethernet controller.

detaileddescription.para: Deactivate the controller and shut down the link. The controller will no longer receive messages, and it cannot send messages anymore.

parameterdescription.para: The Ethernet controller to be deactivated.

simplesect.para: A return code identifying the success/failure of the call.

briefdescription.para: Register a callback for Ethernet transmit acknowledgments.

detaileddescription.para: The handler is called when a previously sent message was successfully transmitted or when the transmission has failed. The original message is identified by the userContext.
NB: Full support in a detailed simulation. In a simple simulation, all messages are immediately positively acknowledged by a receiving controller.

parameterdescription.para: The Ethernet controller for which the message acknowledge callback should be registered.
The user provided context pointer, that is reobtained in the callback.
The handler to be called on reception.
A bit mask defining the transmit status of the message
The handler identifier that can be used to remove the callback.

simplesect.para: A return code identifying the success/failure of the call.

briefdescription.para: Remove a SilKit_EthernetFrameTransmitHandler_t by SilKit_HandlerId on this controller.

parameterdescription.para: The Ethernet controller for which the callback should be removed.
Identifier of the callback to be removed. Obtained upon adding to respective handler.

briefdescription.para: Register a callback for changes of the controller state.

detaileddescription.para: The handler is called when the state of the controller changes. E.g., a call to SilKit_EthernetController_Activate() causes the controller to change from state SilKit_EthernetState_Inactive to SilKit_EthernetState_LinkDown. Later, when the link has been established, the state changes again from SilKit_EthernetState_LinkDown to SilKit_EthernetState_LinkUp. Similarly, the status changes back to SilKit_EthernetState_Inactive upon a call to SilKit_EthernetController_Deactivate().

parameterdescription.para: The Ethernet controller for which the message acknowledge callback should be registered.
The user provided context pointer, that is reobtained in the callback.
The handler to be called on reception.
The handler identifier that can be used to remove the callback.

simplesect.para: A return code identifying the success/failure of the call.

parameterdescription.para: The Ethernet controller for which the callback should be removed.
Identifier of the callback to be removed. Obtained upon adding to respective handler.

briefdescription.para: Register a callback for changes of the link bit rate.

detaileddescription.para: The handler is called when the bit rate of the connected link changes. This is typically the case when a link was successfully established, or the controller was deactivated.

parameterdescription.para: The Ethernet controller for which the bitrate change callback should be registered.
The user provided context pointer, that is reobtained in the callback.
The handler to be called on change.
The handler identifier that can be used to remove the callback.

simplesect.para: A return code identifying the success/failure of the call.

briefdescription.para: Remove a SilKit_EthernetBitrateChangeHandler_t by SilKit_HandlerId on this controller.

parameterdescription.para: The Ethernet controller for which the callback should be removed.
Identifier of the callback to be removed. Obtained upon adding to respective handler.

briefdescription.para: Send an Ethernet frame.

detaileddescription.para: Requires previous activation of the controller and a successfully established link. Also, the entire EthernetFrame must be valid, e.g., destination and source MAC addresses must be valid, ether type and vlan tags must be correct.

These requirements are not enforced in simple simulation. In this case, the message is simply passed on to all connected controllers without performing any check. The user must ensure that a valid frame is provided.
If the frame size is smaller than the minimum of 60 bytes, the frame will be padded with zeros.

parameterdescription.para: The Ethernet controller that should send the frame.
The Ethernet frame to be sent.
The user provided context pointer, that is reobtained in the frame ack handler

simplesect.para: A return code identifying the success/failure of the call.
